Conclusion: Every one of the 16 shared disagreements and 361 key-set differences is assigned a source-backed class. Most are differences between NCBI's XML and flat projections, not arithmetic disagreement. Two flat-only keys are nested alleles intentionally excluded by the top-level allele compatibility export.
